==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Amido
<hw>A*mi"do</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Amide</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Containing, or derived
from, amidogen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Amido acid</b></col>, <cd>an acid in which a portion of
the nonacid hydrogen has been replaced by the amido group. The amido
acids are both basic and acid.</cd> -- <col><b>Amido group</b></col>,
<cd>amidogen, <chform>NH2</chform>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amidogen</ent>⟦br⟧
